The paper deals with unsupervised domain adaptation for semantic segmentation, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel model that involves learning shared discriminative features and classifiers simultaneously, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG and cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of distance loss and stagewise training mechanism, which are common techniques in natural language processing (cs.CL) and multimedia (cs.MM) research.
